<%- include('header', { title: 'Setup Guide', streamer: typeof streamer !== 'undefined' ? streamer : null }) %>

<h2 style="margin-bottom: 8px;">Setup Guide</h2>
<p style="color: #adadb8; margin-bottom: 24px;">Follow these steps to get the bot running on your Discord server. Takes about 5 minutes.</p>

<div class="step">
  <div class="step-number">1</div>
  <div class="step-content">
    <h3>Log in with Discord</h3>
    <p>Click <strong>"Log in with Discord"</strong> on the home page. This creates your account using your Discord identity.</p>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <div class="icon">📸</div>
      <div class="label">Home page — "Log in with Discord" button</div>
      <div>Screenshot coming soon</div>
    </div>
    <div class="tip">The bot only reads your Discord username and avatar — no access to your messages or servers.</div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="step">
  <div class="step-number">2</div>
  <div class="step-content">
    <h3>Link Your Twitch Account</h3>
    <p>From the dashboard, click <strong>"Link Twitch Account"</strong>. This tells the bot which Twitch channel to monitor for live streams and clips.</p>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <div class="icon">📸</div>
      <div class="label">Dashboard — "Link Twitch Account" button</div>
      <div>Screenshot coming soon</div>
    </div>
    <ul>
      <li>You'll be redirected to Twitch to authorize</li>
      <li>The bot only reads your public profile — no special permissions needed</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <div class="icon">📸</div>
      <div class="label">Twitch authorization page</div>
      <div>Screenshot coming soon</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="step">
  <div class="step-number">3</div>
  <div class="step-content">
    <h3>Add the Bot to Your Discord Server</h3>
    <p>Click <strong>"Add Bot to a Server"</strong> from the dashboard. This opens Discord's authorization page in a new tab where you select which server to add the bot to.</p>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <div class="icon">📸</div>
      <div class="label">Dashboard — "Add Bot to Server" button</div>
      <div>Screenshot coming soon</div>
    </div>
    <ul>
      <li>You need <strong>Manage Server</strong> permission in the Discord server</li>
      <li>The bot will request permissions to send messages, embed links, and manage roles</li>
      <li>After authorizing, go back to the dashboard</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <div class="icon">📸</div>
      <div class="label">Discord — Select a server to add the bot</div>
      <div>Screenshot coming soon</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="step">
  <div class="step-number">4</div>
  <div class="step-content">
    <h3>Claim Your Server</h3>
    <p>After adding the bot, your server will appear under <strong>"Available Servers"</strong> on the dashboard. Click <strong>"Claim"</strong> to link it to your account.</p>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <div class="icon">📸</div>
      <div class="label">Dashboard — Available Servers section with "Claim" button</div>
      <div>Screenshot coming soon</div>
    </div>
    <div class="tip">Each server can only be claimed by one user. If someone else has already set up the bot on that server, you won't see it in the list.</div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="step">
  <div class="step-number">5</div>
  <div class="step-content">
    <h3>Add Twitch Channels to Watch</h3>
    <p>Click <strong>"Channels"</strong> on your server, then add any Twitch username you want to monitor. For each channel you can choose:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Live Notifications Channel</strong> — where to send "X is live" alerts</li>
      <li><strong>Clip Notifications Channel</strong> — where to send new clip alerts</li>
    </ul>
    <p style="margin-top: 8px;">You can set different Discord channels for live and clips, or leave one disabled.</p>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <div class="icon">📸</div>
      <div class="label">Twitch Channels page — Add a channel form + watched list</div>
      <div>Screenshot coming soon</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="step">
  <div class="step-number">6</div>
  <div class="step-content">
    <h3>Add YouTube Channels (Optional)</h3>
    <p>Click <strong>"YouTube Channels"</strong> on your server settings to add YouTube channels:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Enter a <strong>YouTube Channel ID</strong> (starts with <code>UC</code>). Find any channel ID at <a href="https://commentpicker.com/youtube-channel-id.php" target="_blank">commentpicker.com</a></li>
      <li>Choose separate Discord channels for <strong>video/shorts notifications</strong> and <strong>live notifications</strong></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <div class="icon">📸</div>
      <div class="label">YouTube Channels page — Add a YouTube channel form</div>
      <div>Screenshot coming soon</div>
    </div>
    <div class="tip">Video/shorts notifications use the free YouTube RSS feed and don't need an API key. Live detection requires a YouTube Data API key set in your account settings.</div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="step">
  <div class="step-number">7</div>
  <div class="step-content">
    <h3>Configure Welcome Messages (Optional)</h3>
    <p>In your server <strong>"Settings"</strong> page, enable the welcome message feature:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Toggle on <strong>Welcome Messages</strong></li>
      <li>Select which channel to send welcome messages to</li>
      <li>Optionally write a custom welcome message</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <div class="icon">📸</div>
      <div class="label">Server Settings — Welcome Message section</div>
      <div>Screenshot coming soon</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="step">
  <div class="step-number">8</div>
  <div class="step-content">
    <h3>Enable Subscriber Role Sync (Optional)</h3>
    <p>This feature automatically gives a Discord role to your Twitch subscribers:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Click <strong>"Enable Sub Sync"</strong> from the dashboard — this authorizes the bot to read your subscriber list</li>
      <li>In your server settings, toggle on <strong>Subscriber Role Sync</strong> and select a role</li>
      <li>Your community members type <code>/link</code> in Discord to connect their Twitch account</li>
      <li>The bot checks every 10 minutes and assigns or removes the role automatically</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <div class="icon">📸</div>
      <div class="label">Server Settings — Subscriber Role Sync section</div>
      <div>Screenshot coming soon</div>
    </div>
    <div class="tip">Make sure the bot's role is <strong>above</strong> the subscriber role in your server's role list (Server Settings &rarr; Roles). The bot can only assign roles lower than its own.</div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="card" style="margin-top: 32px; text-align: center;">
  <h3 style="margin-bottom: 8px;">Ready to get started?</h3>
  <p style="color: #adadb8; margin-bottom: 16px;">The whole setup takes about 5 minutes.</p>
  <a href="/auth/login" class="btn btn-discord" style="font-size: 16px; padding: 12px 24px;">Log in with Discord</a>
</div>

<%- include('footer') %>
